o implement the 8-to-1 selection, mapping 0 to Q[0], 1 to Q[1], ..., 7 to Q[7].\n*   **Error Avoidance:** Ensure the sequential block correctly handles the `enable` condition. Use non-blocking assignments (`<=`) for sequential logic.\n\n**Addressing the Hint:** The hint regarding K-maps and input ordering is for logic minimization, which is not required here as the memory read mechanism (A, B, C) directly selects Q[0] through Q[7], making the multiplexing straightforward.",
